Beginning the first weekend following Labor Day 2021 the US 197 - Dalles Bridge will be closed between Washington and Oregon from 8 p.m. Thursday nights through 6 a.m. Monday mornings for bridge deck replacement work.Note: During the full weekend bridge closures travelers will follow a signed detour using the US 97 Biggs Junction Bridge. Note: Currently travelers can expect to see delays of up to 20 minutes weeknights from 8 p.m. Monday to 6 a.m. Thursday due to single lane closures. During these times traffic will be controlled by flaggers.This work is being performed by ODOT.
